<informationtext name="Information">
<![CDATA[
<p>The Managerial Economics minor is 24 units of upper division ARE coursework. Prerequisites total 28 units and are required. All lower-division preparatory coursework must be completed with minimum C- (or Pass) grades, however, <span class="sc_courseinline"><span class="code_bubble" data-code-bubble="STA 103">STA 103</span></span> must be taken for a letter grade.</p>

<p>All courses to satisfy the minor must be taken for a letter grade, and students must attain a minor GPA of at least a C average (2.000). All upper division courses taken toward minor requirements will be calculated as part of the minor GPA, including courses with F grades that have not been repeated.</p>
<p>A total of two upper division courses (maximum 4 units each) may be taken through UC Study Abroad, all other courses must be taken in residence. Students must seek pre-approval from a Managerial Economics staff advisor for any international courses.</p>
]]>
</informationtext>
